So, this is my first entry and since nothing drastic has happened lately I'll let you in on how my weekend went. Friday was a really slow day and I didn't do much of anything except sit home and try to concentrate on preparing for Saturday. Saturday I arrived at school early Saturday morning (6:30) and took a bus to UWGB for State Solo Ensemble. There I preformed my piano duet with Alex, we got a 1! Then I also participated in double reed choir and because of a high standard judge we received a 2. I was done performing by 10 after 10 and I was ready to leave but I landed up having to fill in for the Wind Ensemble brass choir and help with attendance and percussion equipment. So I was at UWGB well past 5 o'clock. From there I took a bus home and Cora was nice enough to give me a ride so I wouldn't have to walk. Then today, being Mother's Day, I went with my grandma and someother family to brunch. That was interesting, but it always is. Afterwards I came home and have been sitting here doing nothing ever since. I spent most of the day sitting online talking to friends from school! Overall it was a bore-fest. But Now I must get ready to prepare for the long week ahead. Tomorrow I have a read-along with Red Raider Jazz and a softball game. Tuesday is Pulaski vs. Bay Port @ Bay Port for Soccer...again....maybe we will win this time! (Soccer) and Thursday is my Jazz audition..wish me luck! and Friday I am going to Manitowac for the Large Group Festival for BAND! After that I will be going to my last soccer practice to watch movies and then go to Chuck E. Cheese for 8 with the soccer ladies. At 10 all my soccer friends will leave and my band friends will join me for 2 more hours of fun! and Eventually I will get home and sleep to wake up to another day of business. Loretta is graduating from UW-Oshkosh so I have to attend her graduation and Sunday I have a band concert @ 1:30 and a Piano recital @ 6:30. Then my week will start over again!
